page.title: 10MID-SUSSEX ECOLOGY
page.content: {Contains:}The highest point in our block is 250m above sea level at Scaynes Hill,the lowest is on the banks of the river Ouse which is about 10m above sea level.It is quite hilly in places and steep,especially in woodland. {Farming Types:}The main farming in our block is dairy and mixed farms.There are 11 of these in total and are mainly intensive.There are also deciduous and coniferous trees. {Rural features:}The features of the block are mainly undulating woodland. Streams and rivers run through the woodlands and farms.The river Ouse is the largest of the many rivers.There are many footpaths which are in woodland and are available for public use.
